
This configuration drives a standard 3-axis Milling/Laser/Engraving machine using the PRU for
high speed step/dir pulse generation and a StepOneCNC driver board.  The
StepOneCNC configuration is for the a BBB rev.C using the eMMC and HDMI.

There are currently no limit switches configured, so adjust the MIN_LIMIT
and MAX_LIMIT axis settings in the ini file if your printer has less than
? inches of X/ ? inches of Y travel.


Adjust as required for your machine.  Make scale negative to invert any
axis that is moving 'backwards'.

